# Git & Workflow Rules

## Branch Strategy

```
main          → live/published theme (never push directly)
staging       → staging/preview theme
feature/*     → new features, pushed to dev theme
fix/*         → bug fixes
app/*         → app integration work
hotfix/*      → urgent live fixes (merge to main + staging)
```

## Commit Message Format

```
type(scope): short description

Types:
  feat      → new section, block, or feature
  fix       → bug fix
  style     → CSS/visual changes with no logic change
  chore     → schema, config, or dependency updates
  app       → third-party app integration
  refactor  → code restructure with no behavior change
  perf      → performance improvement
  docs      → documentation only

Examples:
  feat(section): add sticky announcement bar with countdown timer
  fix(cart): resolve app block overlap on mobile drawer
  style(hero): update CTA button hover state
  chore(schema): add border radius setting to card section
  app(judge-me): integrate star ratings into collection card
  perf(images): add lazy loading to all below-fold product images
```

## Shopify CLI Workflow

```bash
# Start local dev (hot reload against dev theme)
shopify theme dev --store your-store.myshopify.com --theme <dev-theme-id>

# Push specific files only (safer than pushing everything)
shopify theme push --theme <dev-theme-id> --only sections/hero.liquid

# Pull latest from a theme (sync before starting work)
shopify theme pull --theme <live-theme-id>

# List all themes and their IDs
shopify theme list

# Push to staging for QA
shopify theme push --theme <staging-theme-id>
```

## Before Every Commit

- [ ] Tested on dev theme via `shopify theme dev`
- [ ] No hardcoded product IDs, handles, or prices
- [ ] App blocks preserved in any modified section schemas
- [ ] No `settings_data.json` changes accidentally staged
- [ ] CSS classes namespaced with `.theme-`
- [ ] New strings added to `locales/en.default.json`

## Pull Request Checklist

- [ ] Branch is off `main` (or `staging`)
- [ ] PR title follows commit message format
- [ ] Tested on a dev/staging theme
- [ ] App integrations verified (blocks still appear in editor)
- [ ] Mobile QA done
- [ ] No console errors introduced
